      "delta": [
        "Baseline: fully serverless-no-VPC, ~$0 idle — Lambda + DynamoDB on-demand + S3 + HTTP API Gateway",
        "Single-AZ implicit (Lambda/DynamoDB are regional but single-table, no replica config)",
        "CloudFront caches gallery/SEO reads at edge — primary read-scale mechanism",
        "Corpus loaded from S3 into Lambda memory per generation invocation (brute-force cosine, no vector DB)",
        "WAF rate-based rule protects generation endpoint from abuse",
        "Observability: CloudWatch Logs + key alarms (Lambda errors/throttles/duration, APIGW 5xx) → SNS email"
      ],
      "tradeoffs": [
        "No multi-AZ failover: a Lambda/DynamoDB/APIGW regional disruption causes downtime (acceptable per brief)",
        "Cold starts on idle Lambda (~200–500ms) add latency before the LLM call — negligible given 1–2 min generation time",
        "Corpus blob loaded per invocation adds ~10–50ms S3 read at small corpus size; acceptable until hundreds of vectors",
        "No read replicas or DAX — hot gallery reads served by CloudFront cache; cache miss hits DynamoDB directly",
        "Single operator Cognito user pool: no group-based RBAC, sufficient for one operator"
      ],
